The paper deals with clustering algorithms and their modification to handle incomplete data with missing features. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining. Specifically, the paper proposes a new dissimilarity measure and modifies traditional clustering algorithms to handle missing features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also discusses simulation techniques for missingness, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
